<!-- Card 1: What is an EIR --><div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:18px;">
<div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:8px;">What is an EIR?</div>
<div style="color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">The <strong>Exchange Information Requirements (EIR)</strong> sets out the Owner’s information needs for this project. It defines <strong>what information</strong> is required, <strong>why</strong> it’s needed, and <strong>how</strong> it will be delivered and used across the project lifecycle. It supports tendering, coordination, verification, and a successful handover to the Owner.</div>
</div>
<!-- Card 2: Who is this for --><div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:18px;">
<div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:8px;">Who is this for?</div>
<ul style="margin:0 0 0 18px;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">
<li>
<strong>Owners</strong> who need the right information for operations and handover</li>
<li>
<strong>Consultants</strong> defining information requirements and delivery rules</li>
<li>
<strong>Contractors</strong> responding to tender requirements and delivering structured outputs</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Note: Assignment use --><div style="margin-top:12px;background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #dbe6f3; border-left:5px solid #009ef5;border-radius:14px;padding:14px 16px;"><div style="min-width:0;">
<div style="font-weight:700;color:#1c2430;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:14px;">Note (assignment use)</div>
<div style="color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">
<p>This<span style="font-size: 14px;"> EIR template is <strong>pre-filled</strong> for the assignment. </span>Work through the template section by section and complete the highlighted Smart Fields where prompted.</p>
<p>Some sections will also guide you to carry out specific actions (for example, structuring information requirements in Scope Module). In those cases, simply follow the instructions provided in that section.</p>
</div>
